      • recordsChangedAfterLSN

        public OLogSequenceNumber recordsChangedAfterLSN(OLogSequenceNumber lsn,
                                                 OutputStream stream,
                                                 Set<String> includeClusterNames,
                                                 OCommandOutputListener outputListener)
        This method finds all the records which were updated starting from (but not including) current LSN and write result in provided output stream. In output stream will be included all thw records which were updated/deleted/created since passed in LSN till the current moment. Deleted records are written in output stream first, then created/updated records. All records are sorted by record id. Data format:
        1. Amount of records (single entry) - 8 bytes
        2. Record's cluster id - 4 bytes
        3. Record's cluster position - 8 bytes
        4. Delete flag, 1 if record is deleted - 1 byte
        5. Record version , only if record is not deleted - 4 bytes
        6. Record type, only if record is not deleted - 1 byte
        7. Length of binary presentation of record, only if record is not deleted - 4 bytes
        8. Binary presentation of the record, only if record is not deleted - length of content is provided in above entity
        Parameters:
        lsn - LSN from which we should find changed records
        stream - Stream which will contain found records
        includeClusterNames - Array of cluster ids to include from the export
        Returns:
        Last LSN processed during examination of changed records, or null if it was impossible to find changed records: write ahead log is absent, record with start LSN was not found in WAL, etc.
        See Also:
        OGlobalConfiguration.STORAGE_TRACK_CHANGED_RECORDS_IN_WAL
